Corruption and judiciary settlement are among the issues raised by civil society before EU bodies and started to be tackled in a determined way by the new government elected last year. Other issues are related to or taken over by European institutions such as the fight against oligarchy and against shady deals with energy investments by some businesses owners, namely Maria Grapini. Contracts with private companies for waste treatment plant have been cancelled and a decision on its distribution was taken by European Court of Auditors, who informed national institutions of the irregularities. Are mobile signal in the country still poor? Romania has indeed a large network of paved and asphalted roads and asphalted railway despite the necessary funds of which Europe is a source.

Roads are now more than a half dedicated to trans-European transport corridors, who reach the nearest port or industrial zone. Railways are a little behind on this, too bad the Eurasian backbone could profit of stronger links with the East. Subtitles by the Amara.org community
